an class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/26/03 1:23:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=551.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Mastery of Pain: Worth it?</span><hr size=1> Before I dump the 3 points into Aug Dex II, and then MoP.<br>
<br>
Does it add that much more damage?<br>
<br>
Would I be better off with Aug Str II instead, now that caps are about to change? <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.regal-image.com/customgraphics/grimnorbloodsong.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gisborne>gisborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 248<br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/26/03 2:04:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=551.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mastery of Pain: Worth it?</span><hr size=1> IMO MoPain is not very good. It adds about 1.25% to your overall damage in RvR, as crits are capped at 50%. 5% more chance to do a 1-50% crit just isn't that appealing. <br>
<br>
However, since Aug Dex is the prerequisite for MoParry as well you'll probably end up getting it some time anyway. I will, but not higher than lvl 1 or 2.<br>
 <p>Eka, lvl 50 skald Percival</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=torpidanima>TorpidAnima</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/26/03 5:00:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=551.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Optimal STR and other caps is still 300.  Going over is dimished in gains so bad its not even worth it.  Although, 300 charisma sounds pretty damn nice <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I myself have MoPain III and would never spec out of it.  I crit like mad in PvE and RvR.  Being that our DD's are resisted so much this is pretty much our only option for more dmg as a skald.  Some love it and others won't even think about having it.  However, I am one that will say Mastery of Pain II or III is a f'n must have for a skald <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Torpid Anima - TDA - Merlin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=emblurr@teamskald>Emblurr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/26/03 10:50:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=551.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> I agree, big crits win fights. Though this is more beneficial to people who spec high in weapon and have a good weapon and rr5. Because they bigger the hit the bigger the potential crit can be. I'm even thinking of going mastery of pain IV because of it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kluk@teamskald>Kluk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/27/03 4:06:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=551.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> MoP</span><hr size=1> Actually MOP is more usefull than a regular 1.5% increase in damage.<br>
<br>
The point is when you crit it's basically a free 'weak' hit, and with a bit of luck it can really win a fight where you'd have lost otherwise, I'm a fan of frontloading damage so it's defenitly a RA I won't drop. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=amstellight>Amstel Light</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/27/03 7:52:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=551.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: MoP</span><hr size=1> I have MoP3 and I crit every fourth swing on average.  When swinging a slow 2h, it will do some insane crits.  After hitting with both shouts, I have one shot lvl50 casters a few times which I could not have done without the crits.  That being said...i'm not sure MoP3 is worth the 6 points...but MoP1 and 2 are must gets IMO.  <br>
<br>
I know you use a 1h most of the time grim which means you swing and hit more often than I do.  Which, in turn, means you will have more chances to crit in a fight than I would.  <br>
<br>
I have used the TG 1h skald axe in duels a few times (3.3 spd) and its funny to have people ask how you hit them for 300 unbuffed.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Sideshow lvl50 Skald<br>
Palomides <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kjeld>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 244<br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/27/03 10:50:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=551.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Well</span><hr size=1> I do agree that in RvR, a big hit every now and then that can potentially be a battle winner if you are lucky is better than a flat 1.5% dps increase.<br>
That been said, it's imho a mid-low priority RA, for relatively high ranking skalds (below IP, purge, tireless/LW, probably hp/con boosts ...).<br>
The very good thing about this RA is that it is the same requisit than MoParry. If you take Aug dex II and have the extra points ... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whorde>whorde</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/27/03 7:02:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=551.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well</span><hr size=1> i have mop3.  one of these days when there's a dragon respec stone floating around i'm going to switch it for mop2 + empty mind 1.<br>
<br>
that being said, i consider mop2 to be absolutely critical.  people on this board like to go on and on about 1% this and 2% that, the truth of the matter is that doing 1% more damage doesn't win you any fights.  ever.  i do 250 to 600 damage per swing.  doing 1% more per hit is not going to kill them where i wouldn't have otherwise.  getting an extra 150 damage crit will.<br>
<br>
that is why crits are useful and aug str is crap.  crits are compartmentalized so they periodically impact the outcome.  adding 3 damage to your hits is utterly irrelevant.<br>
<br>
this is actually very easy to test.  go find a level 5 shaman with less than 4 aug.  pay them 20 gold to go to emain and stand around at the pk for 10 minutes.  have them buff you with Minor Force of the Deep, level 1 aug spec 0.7 dps buff.  go rvr.  see how much that uber 3 damage per hit helps you.  then get mad since you wasted your 20 gold and 20 minutes of your day.  hahahaha. <br>
<br>
Phleet <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gisborne>gisborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 249<br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/27/03 10:22:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=551.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well</span><hr size=1> So you're saying we shouldn't bother capping str or +axe on our SC templates because it's worthless? Thanks for the advice.<br>
<br>
You guys make it sound like getting MoPain will magically make you crit like a mad man. 5% is 5%, not 50%. MoPain 1 will mean that 2/3 of the crits you see will have happened anyway. MoPain 2 means 1/2 of them will have happened anyway.<br>
<br>
MoPain isn't worthless but paying 6 pts the MoPain 3 vs. MoPain 2 is a big waste, especially if you don't have IP, Purge, AoM, Toughness, Aug Con, etc out of the way already. <p>Eka, lvl 50 skald Percival</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=emblurr@teamskald>Emblurr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/28/03 12:11:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=551.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> It's not a big waste..what else are you going to spend them on? Fury of the gods? <br>
<br>
Also you don't need IP, purge to do well in rvr. Remember something by itself may not appear to make much difference but when you add a lot of those things up they make a big difference.<br>
<br>
eg<br>
racial resists<br>
starting stats<br>
sc armour<br>
alchd items<br>
100 qual weapons<br>
rr5<br>
RA<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kjeld>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 245<br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/28/03 3:06:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=551.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hahaha</span><hr size=1> what else are you going to spend them on? Fury of the gods? <br>
