 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimmytheskald>Grimmytheskald</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/28/03 7:20:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=551.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hahaha</span><hr size=1> I don't use 1-hand exclusively, I usually carry it around to attack first.  Casters are my main target, and they get the one hander.  When I fight mele's, I break out the two-hander.<br>
<br>
Thanks for the advice, to this point I've spent a lot of points on passive RA's that increased my survivability.  Now that I'm RR6, I have some to spend on offense, so I thought I would ask how effective this big investment is.  Thank you.<br>
<br>
On IP and Purge: I have them, I use them nearly every time I play, and I wouldn't trade either for anything.<br>
<br>
I think it pays to be carefull how you spend your RA's when they now take about 60-80k rp's to get <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.regal-image.com/customgraphics/grimnorbloodsong.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whorde>whorde</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/28/03 12:53:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=551.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hahaha</span><hr size=1> for the record, skalds in fact do not have a 5% chance to crit.  before RAs i didn't even know skalds could crit in rvr, i had fumbled 2 or 3 times in the 500k worth of rvr i had done but i had never critted.<br>
<br>
mastery of pain makes it so you DO crit.<br>
<br>
critical hits win fights.  aug str doesn't.  you can be a prick and act snooty over your 1% all you want about this issue, but the facts do not change.<br>
<br>
